There is a chance that `thread` is null when calling `thread.interrupt()`.

``` Scala
  override def cancel(): Unit = this.synchronized {
    _cancelled = true
    if (thread != null) {
      thread.interrupt()
    }
  }
```

Should put `thread = null` into a `synchronized` block to fix the race condition.

